Case called at 11:28 am [Clerk SH] (Case was scheduled for FSSC)
Defendant Policarpio  Villanueva in court, in-custody, with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. DA Susan Victoria Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

On Motion of the State, the Court strikes the repeater enhancer

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered knowingly, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, orders JOC entered.

Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 10 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence consecutive to any other sentence in being, no electronic monitoring and may be served in the prison system
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--Court orders statutory costs, fees, and all other court financial obligations including $33 subpoena fees be entered into civil judgment
--Court orders $150 restitution, payable to Amy Moss, be entered into civil judgment
--Court determines that Mr. Villanueva has already submitted DNA Sample and does not order collection

Felony Firearm/Voting Restrictions Warnings Given

case called at 1:22pm, [MK]
Defendant Policarpio Villanueva appears via videoconferencing from Fox Lake Correctional Institution, in custody. DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.  

On agreement of Mr. Villanueva, the Court finds that the videoconferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 

Right to counsel given. Mr. Villanueva indicates that he knows the process for contacting the PD Office in Jefferson to seek representation by counsel. 
Constitutional rights given. 
Service of Complaint admitted; the Court reads the Criminal Complaint to Mr. Villanueva.  The charge and maximum penalties are recited. 
Preliminary Hearing time limits are waived by both parties.

The Court requires a $5,000  signature bond, with conditions:
--not to have direct or indirect contact with Amy R. Moss
--no presence at the Boughton Street apartments located at 1153 Boughton Street in Watertown 
--not to engage in any acts or threats of violence
--booking at the Jefferson County Sheriff's Department is to occur before release on this case 

The Court informs the parties that this case will transfer to Branch III/Judge Wambach on January 1st. 
recess 1:37pm. 


NEXT: (1) clerk is to mail the Right to Attorney/PD contact information form to Mr. Villanueva, (2) Pretrial Conference on 12/17/14 at 11:20am  (2) schedule Preliminary Hearing in Branch III in January (State will need to prepare writ-- Mr. Villanueva is in the WSPS until June 2015)
